## Why this matters

Most systems fail due to:
- uncontrolled drift
- instability under adversarial input
- over-constrained freezing

ASV3 demonstrates:
- bounded evolution without collapse
- adaptive constraint enforcement
- real-time stability under stress

This makes it suitable as a safety/control layer for AI and autonomous systems.

Input Signal
     ↓
Spectral Analysis (SDF)
     ↓
Phase Detection (Δ, VRA)
     ↓
TSC Coherence Layer
     ↓
Lyapunov Energy (V)
     ↓
Projection + Barrier (Invariant Enforcement)
     ↓
Adaptive Budget Update
     ↓
Stable Output

ASV3 provides system-level invariant enforcement.
IGAS provides state-space control for LLMs.

Together they form a unified stability architecture.

